1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,145
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,095 --> 00:00:10,421
First, you do a warm-up: Show that formulas are instructions for Excel.

3
00:00:10,421 --> 00:00:14,578
Say: equals means Excel, please work this out.

4
00:00:14,578 --> 00:00:19,130
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:19,130 --> 00:00:27,649
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Type =2+3, press Enter, then change the numbers and try again.

6
00:00:27,649 --> 00:00:33,709
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type a formula to add 2 and 3.

7
00:00:33,709 --> 00:00:42,309
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Return to iLearn, mark the lesson complete, and open the certificate together.

8
00:00:42,309 --> 00:00:45,421
Staff will ask you what you are most proud of.

9
00:00:45,421 --> 00:00:47,972
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:47,972 --> 00:00:52,513
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

